  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries around the world. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key aspects of AML regulations typically include:\n\n1. Customer identification and verification requirements\n2. Reporting of suspicious transactions\n3. Maintaining transaction records\n4. Implementing internal compliance programs\n5. Screening against terrorist and sanctions lists\n\nMany countries have specific AML laws, and international organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) provide global standards for combating money laundering.",
